          },
          "text": "Last month, an 11-year-old Ubuntu fan named Boston, sent us this heartfelt letter, sharing how Ubuntu inspires him every day.\n\nHis words touched our entire team, and his hand-drawn Tux the Penguin stole our hearts 🐧🧡\n\nMark Shuttleworth, Canonical CEO and Founder, wrote back, encouraging him to keep exploring, learning, and creating with open source technology. We also sent Boston a special gift package along with the letter 🎁\n\nOn the 24th of January, the world celebrates the International Day of Education, so please join us in celebrating the curiosity and passion of young learners like Boston.\n\nWe believe education and technology go hand in hand, empowering people of all ages to dream big and innovate. Boston’s story reminds us of the incredible impact open source can have on young minds and the future they’ll shape.\n\nHere’s to nurturing the spark of curiosity and supporting the next generation of innovators! 🌟\n\n#educationday #internationaldayofeducation #opensource #ubuntu"
        },
